This worked for me... It seems like their documentation is outright wrong on this part

```js
ws.addConditionalFormatting({
    ref: "A1:B4",
    rules: [
        {
            type: "dataBar",
            minLength: 10,
            cfvo: [{type: "min"}, {type: "max"}],
            color: {argb: "FFFF5050"}
        }
    ]
});
```

I found out from here: https://www.gitmemory.com/issue/exceljs/exceljs/1163/836431274

This databar works for me: values are clamped to -20,000...20,000 and show red for negative, green for positive, with a dark gray axis in the middle.

   ```js
 ws.addConditionalFormatting({
        ref: `D2:D${sheet.rowCount}`,
        rules: [
            {
                type: "dataBar",
                gradient: false,
                border: false,
                negativeBarColorSameAsPositive: false,
                cfvo: [ { type:'num', value:-20000 }, { type:'num', value:20000 } ],
                color: { argb:'40DD4A' },
                negativeFillColor: { argb:'FF0000' },
                axisColor: { argb:'4D4D4D' }
            }
        ]
    });
```

I figured this out by examining the code here: https://github.com/exceljs/exceljs/blob/ec92cb3b898bdf7f806ff9d7b8370c955ee8ba20/lib/xlsx/xform/sheet/cf-ext/databar-ext-xform.js#L36-L59

and comparing with an "unzipped" XLSX file.
